    "My Review":
      "Remember the huge dissapointment called Harry Potter and the Cursed child we waited for for 9 years? Well, this was the same (possibly worse), but I was waiting for it for ELEVEN years. <br/><br/>You have no idea how excited I was for this book. So excited that I've never really realised what this book actually means - over 600 pages in Edward's head. Over 600 pages of creepyness, stalking, selfishness, self-pity, self-hate and huge disrespect towards Bella. I've never read more frustrating book - I've actually screamed several times. Also, there was no other book that made me feel so uncomfortable like this one. Have you read/watched thriller You? Well, I didn´t but I know what is it about - and this is a vampire version of it. EDWARD OILS BELLA'S WINDOWS(!!!) so he won't wake her up while he's breaking into her room because he's nervous meteorite could hit her in her sleep (!!!!!!). And then during sunny days he's following her 24/7 without her knowledge. Not to mention he constantly listens to every single thought anyone has about her. If this isn't creepy af for you, I don't know what is. <br/><br/>Reading his thoughts and his overthinking full of self-pity, selfishness and hate was torture. Being in his mind was almost as bad as being in mine. If this was annoying for you in Twilight series... this is 1000x worse. But it was his ignorance, his complete disrespect towards Bella's wishes that made me scream the most. It's not just her wish to become a vampire - he simply ignores EVERYTHING she wants and he doesn't. Because ofc, she has no idea what she actually wants - only he knows what´s best for her. Ignorant fucking moron. <br/>Not to mention he spent over 600 pages to complain about everything.<br/>I've never been a huge fan of him - altho I've always been team Edward and that didn't change (despite everything I realise they are kinda made for each other) - but now I despise him like no other character ever. <br/><br/>However, when we ignore Edward (which is almost completely impossible in this case), I'm glad I read this (altho there's no chance I'll read it again). It gave me more insight into Bella's character - it was interesting to see her through someone else´s eyes, to see layers of her character that were hidden from readers until now. It made me really like her. And I actually think she deserves better than obsessive control freak.<br/>But my favourite parts of this book were Alice and Emmett that had more space that possibly in all four previous books combined. Because of Edward´s mind reading we FINALLY find out how exactly Alice's visions work and how reliable they actually are. And how sweet and kind she actually is. <br/>We've never actually got to properly know Emmett (except for few funny lines) - he's incredibly sweet and pure and my favourite character of this series.<br/><br/>Also, it turned out, Jasper was awfully overlooked in the series. His powers, his strength were never really explored and here he kinda blew my mind. He didn´t had enough space tho. <br/>On the other hand, Rosalie had more space then she should've - she was annoying me almost as much as Edward. <br/>Speaking of Edward, back to his obsession with Bella. Because of his 24/7 stalking schedule... he doesn't spend that much time with his family as I hoped so. All Cullens (perhaps except for Rose) are million times more interesting than Edward. Yet, there was lack of scenes with them. (Because Edward thinking THE SAME THINGS over and over and over and over again are apparently more important.) Scenes with them were highlights of this book.<br/><br/>There were few other highlights too - some details that weren't properly explained (or they were simply ignored) in Twilight (like why Edward didn´t read Alice's story from James's mind immediately or what happened to that rapist cunt from Port Angeles) or some memories from his earlier years that were quite interesting. And his mind reading was sometimes interesting as well - such a shame he usually<br/><br/>Overall, this book mostly made me mad and I'll try to forget most of it. (I'm gonna remember only those useful and interesting information.)<br/>I wouldn´t mind more Twilight books tho. Like New moon from Jacob´s view. Or anything about Alice. Emmett. Jasper. Renesmee. <br/>(I´m also taking more about Beau and Edythe.)<br/><br/>Good thing I didn't waste any money on this. But I'm really affraid this book ruined my love of this series. I hope not.",
