      'I absolutely LOVE It´s always sunny in Philadelphia. The best sitcom and one of the best shows ever made with an absolutely brilliant and clever writting. <br/>However, these  characters work better on camera rather than on page. Some essays felt flat and they weren´t that funny or interesting. On the other hand, some were absolutely brilliant and hilarious. Typical characters. My favoutite essay was <i>Here´s how straight I am.</i> by Mac which was a pure brilliant masterpiece.<br/><br/>This was my favourite part of that essay: <br/><i>I´m not against homosexuality, though. I say to each his own. You´re free to do whatever you want. But you shouldn´t be able to get married, because marriage is sacred. And if gays are able to get married, then what´s next? People marrying watermelons? However, this is a free country and you should have all the same rights as us straight people, except for certain rights that you shouldn´t have because you´re gay. And even though God has a plan for you and He made you the way you are, he´s sending you to hell, because you also had free will. Okay, Dennis just told me that last part doesn´t make sense so I had to explain to him that that´s where faith plays into all this. Now, I don´t have time to explain why faith trumps facts right now, so why don´t you go ahead and pull out the big book and have God explain that one Himself. In conclusion, just always remember that even though God is sending you to hell, He loves you and He always will.</i><br/><br/>This part is absolutely brilliant, because it´s a very accurate reflection of "logic" and hypocrisy of religion* and I had numerous online discussions like that. **<br/><br/>* I don´t have a problem with faith or God, I have a problem with a hypocrisy and when people are forcing me their religion. Or when our government is using religion to make laws. Fuck you. <br/>** yes, I know. One would think I have learnt my lesson after first hundred online discussions about the same thing.',
