    "My Review":
      "Oh, this book... There's a lot I have on my mind right now. <br/>First of all, this is 'Big little lies' type of mystery. To be honest, we saw story like this a billion times. Group of friends, one of them has a big secret and then something big happens. Nothing unique but I still kind of enjoyed reading. It was quick read and something different from what I read lately.<br/><br/>The main issueI had with ths book are characters because thay are terribly written. So, oficially there're five main characters. Jonas is that mysterious one with big secret... And the only one who you didn't know what to expect from. The only character with a little developement. The only one who was interesting.<br/>Than there is Soleil who fell in love with him, supported him, googled him... <br/>Penny is the one who tought she's not worth of anything.<br/>Miri is the one who worships the Godess. <br/>Fatima is the Godess, the author of books who always says something wise (and full of cliché) and everyone is obsessed by her. <br/>I'd like to tell you something more but that's the full characteristic of these characters. They might look like main characters but you can really tell everything about them in one sentence because that they became background. So Jonas was the only one I cared about. The rest are just a tool for telling story without any personality.<br/><br/>I loved there's several point of views, everyone has a chance to tell their side of that story and it's not confusing. I liked there are different forms of telling what happened - interviews, emails and excerpts from a book. But I found that excerpts very boring and badly written. I realy doubt somebdy would really publish it because (like I read in one of the reviews here on Goodreads and I absolutely agree) it felt like it was written by someone who never wrote anything in her life. Also there are several mistakes there. I can understand it must be difficult to have a novel inside a novel but still... In excerpts there are sometimes names from a 'real' story.<br/>Writing in that book is very average. I was hoping it's because it's her first book... But it's her second so nah.<br/><br/>Than the end. I kind of liked the plot twist but I can't say it was unexpected. That thing crossed my mind several times and it made sense, I just wished it's not true.<br/>But I don't like how book ended.<br/><br/>Still, this book was addicting. I didn't want to stop reading. I needed to know what happened and what will happen. <br/><br/>And do I recommend it? Actually, yes. Good for relax, you don't have to think about it too much... But don't expect anything.",
