      "This book was my most anticipated book of this year. Both Adam´s books – More happy than not and History is all you left me – belong to my all time favorites and Adam is my favorite author. So I had pretty high expectations. I´m so happy and grateful I could read it two months earlier.<br/>I wasn´t disappointed.<br/><br/>How could I describe his books? So many emotions! No one can write as beautiful but also as sad books as Adam. I must admit this one was a little slow sometimes (but this book takes place in one day so...) It´s so funny and adorable, but also heartbreaking. I liked this book a little less than previous ones but it´s still absolutely fantastic and I love it. You will think about this book a lot, it´s so powerful. You will think about your life, death and everything between. It has a great message.<br/><br/><b><i>Twelve hours ago I received the phone call telling me I´m going to die today, and I´m more alive now than I was back then. </i></b><br/><br/>Also, I really love the title (and the cover) of this book. Both are very eye-catching. It´s very weird to read a book and know how it ends but you  still hope it ends differently. You will be scared because you won´t be psychically prepared to say goodbye to your new favorite characters. You will probably fall in love with botrh of them, they are such fantastic characters! But I love Mateo more. He´s the kindest and most adorable character ever! I wanted to hug him and not let  go. Tell him everything would be fine. He was like a lost puppy.<br/><br/>This book kind of reminded me of another book I absolutely love – Aristotle and Dante discover the secrets of the universe. Mostly because of that wonderful friendship. Also I haven´t read about such beautiful relationship since I read that book.<br/><br/>I need another story with these characters with alternative ending. They both live at the end. They deserve it, I love them so much! <br/>Adam just broke my heart again and destroyed me. I was so close to crying! <br/>As always it was so sensitive, unique and beautiful and I know he put a piece of him inside. I love his writing style and I would read anything by him. I´m sure I would tear up just reading his shopping list. <br/>You WANT TO read this book. (All of his books.) Trust me. They´re the best.<br/><br/><b><i>Thank you so much HarperTeen and Edelweiss for this ARC. </i></b>",
