      "I fell in love with this book immediately. Adam has a fantastic and brilliant writing style. If you haven´t heard about him yet you certainly will. I´m sure that everyone who loves young adult literature will know him one day. Just like everyone knows the names Sarah J. Mass, Cassandra Clare or John Green. He certainly is talented enough for it.<br/>This story is written so realistically, you feel like you're living inside of it. It made me feel so many emotions I thought it will kill me, but I couldn’t stop reading it because it was so perfect. My heart was breaking more than I could count, I was hurting, I suffered but it was such a beautiful and powerful story that it was worth it. I had tears in my eyes. And then I felt empty like there was a giant gaping hole in my chest I could never fill again. (Last time it happened when I was reading More happy than not. Do you see what Adam Silvera does to me?)  <br/><br/>After reading two of his books Adam Silvera became one of my all time favorite authors and I can´t wait for his next books and the physical copy of this one. I can’t wait to re-read it one day.<br/>Go read this book and once you’re at it, read MHTN as well, you won’t regret it. They are little treasures of young adult literature. I knew from the beginning that this book doesn’t deserve 5 out of 5 stars but at least 10.",
